Definition
Floor adhesives are specialized bonding agents used to attach various types of flooring materials, including vinyl, laminate, carpet, tile, and hardwood, to different substrates such as concrete, wood, and metal. These adhesives are designed to provide strong adhesion, durability, and resistance to environmental factors like moisture and temperature fluctuations. With advancements in formulation technology, modern floor adhesives offer improved performance and versatility for both residential and commercial applications.
